description: Hawkeye needs a date for an Avengers picnic, but just once he’d like to meet a regular girl who doesn’t punch holes through walls or jet off to Saturn for the weekend. But how does one go about meeting a normal girl when living the life of a super hero? The solution seems to be an online dating service called Lover’s Leap, but when Hawkeye accidentally downloads a wealth of sensitive Avengers information onto the website, which (dang!) turns out to be a scam site run by Batroc the Leaper, it’s going to take the combined fighting might of the Avengers to get Hawkeye out of this jam! Well, at least some of the Avengers. Please don’t tell the others about this, okay?
name: Lover's Leaper

description: The true enemy stands revealed and in a twisted past with no order, two teams of heroes make their way under the Atlantic ocean to confront the enemies of freedom who are planning their next move behind a wall built around Europe. But even with the help of Sgt. Fury and his Howling Commandos, plus Black Panther, it may be too late to stop the end of everything.
name: Past Tense

description:
Maxi-Man declares war on Mr. Miracle.

After being videotaped saving a group of office workers from a fire, the word is out that Bailey, NH has its own Superhero in the form of Mister Miracle. This pleases Oberon's new business partner, since there's not such thing as bad publicity. Even less pleased is the down-on-his-luck crime fighter, Maxi-Man.

Oberon continues spraying customers with Scott's mystery cleaning agent, an act which strangely goes unnoticed by the EPA. While Scott is at work, Barda discusses animal experimentation with Kathy, the next door neighbor.

Miracle and Maxi-Man have their first altercation after both try to interrupt the same purse-snatching. After each trying to convince the other to leave town, they have another altercation at the site of a traffic accident. Thankfully, one of the traffic victims convinces the two to stop their foolishness. Realizing that he isn't quite ready for a full-time hero gig, Maxi-Man leaves town for parts unknown.
name: This Town Isn't Big Enough For the Both of Us!

description:
Oberon's new invention creates a lot of attention at Scott Free's Fix-It Shop.

Just when Scott thinks that he finally has his life in Bailey in order, he arrives at work to find that Oberon has been hawking one of his chemicals as a "miracle cleaning". Worse yet, the dwarf secured financing through the unscrupulous Maxwell Lord. Lord, in turn, hires the even less scrupulous Funky Flashman to handle promotion of the sales.

In another part of town, Barda (who is wearing what is by far her most pleasant outfit of the entire series) is attending an animal rights meeting to learn more about the mysterious monkey from issue 9.

Scott thows on his costume in an effort to avoid Oberon and Brown, only to be accosted by mysterious mercenaries who accuse him of stealing something of great value. With little explanation of how (as usual), Scott escapes their trap and watches as the baffled mercenaries escape.
name: What? And Give Up Show Business?

description:
Funky Flashman and the Head scheme against Mr. Miracle.

The mystery object of issue 11 is finally revealed.It is none other than "The Head"! While Comicdom has no shortage of brain-in-jar or box type characters, none is quite as forgettable as The Head.

Flashman continues to harass Scott into signing restrictive contracts, but both are interrupted by the return of issue 11's mercenaries.In another part of Bailey, Barda joins a protest against the Serenity Fields R&D company.The crowd is interrupted by a conspicuously devil-haired representative, whom Barda is more than willing to break in half.Kathy Ferbel interrupts her, but Barda is still looking to act rather than just protest.

Battle continues to ensue and Free's Fixit shop.The mercs want the Head, the Head wants out, and Miracle just wants to be left in piece.The conflict escalates until the entire block of shops is trashed by Scott's menagerie of unusual repair jobs.With irate neighbors looking for reparations and little money to placate them, the escape artist signs Flashman's contract.
name: Head of the Clash

description:
While touring the galaxy in his super escape artist show, Mr. Miracle runs afoul of Lobo!

So Mister Miracle has signed his contract. He'll throw on the costume, do a few shows, hawk some cleaner, make some dough, and pay back his neighbors for all the destruction from issue #12.

What could possibly go wrong?

Turns out, Scott signed a contract to perform on other planets at the whim of intergalactic-trader Manga Khan! The cruise is pleasant enough, but the Doom-esque antics of Manga start to chafe. During their voyage, Khan uses his electro-nets to gather energy for his ship. In one such casting, the golden-plated traveler accidentally nabs a pair of dolphins. A pair of space dolphins to be precise. A pair of very familiar space dolphins.

On Earth, Barda deals with the arrival of several pallets of Miracle-Misters, as well as the continued snoopings of young Wally and Andy. Unbeknownst to her, Manga has created a doppleganger of Miracle in order to keep the JLI from being concerned about Scott's disappearance. This duplicate, strangely enough, is aware that he is married to Barda but has no knowledge of Miracle's secret identity of Scott Free.

Lobo arrives on Manga's ship. The great golden Khan pleads with Scott to placate the galactic bounty hunter, which the escape artist is able to do with reasonable skill. Unfortunately for all involved, Manga's robots bartered the space dolphins away without their master's knowledge.
name: A Fine Kettle of Fish

description:
Mr. Miracle and Lobo team up to save the dolphins while Big Barda deals with two kids who have discovered Mr. Miracle's secret identity.

After an altercation that ends up releasing Lord Manga from his robotic shell, Scott convinces Lobo that he will assist the bounty hunter in locating the missing dolphins. The creatures were traded to a green hued projected entity. Coordinates in hand, Scott and Lobo take off for the projection's origin. The dolphins are found on a nearby planet, merrily grazing on yellow rocks that fall on its surface. As Lobo tries to retrieve his pets, the plants themselves attack to defend the creatures. Miracle escapes the traps with little effort, and the green projection is forced to explain himself. The planet and the dolphins share a symbiosis. The green rocks harm the surface, but nourish the creatures.

(psst, it was Mogo)

Barda grows fed up with the antics of Wally and Andy, punctuating her feelings with a minor earthquake. The two children only compound her frustrations with her missing husband and her continued interest in the local animal testing. A supposed sympathetic party arrives at her doorstep, offering her critical information regarding the defenseless animals of the world.
name: Eating Pain

description:
On the planet Colossopolis, Scott is captured by a giant and forced to do battle in the Maze of Danger against the Foes of Five.  Scott has little trouble fighting off the varyingly armed and skilled enemies.  The strange giant starts throwing a tantrum, but calms down when his mother arrives to console him.

In a more serous part of the universe, the sinister Mr. Gashe goads Barda into violent action.  In her grief, she tries to call Scott at the JLI mansion.  Unfortunately, the Miracle-android has no knowledge of Scott's secret identity (only his marriage) and behaves as though he has no idea what Mrs. Free is talking about.  Gashe leaves a bomb with Barda and suggest that the only course of action is a violent one.
name: Power Fantasy

description:
Still stuck on the planet Colossopolis, Scott, L-Ron, Funky Flashman, Oberon, and the insufferable Manga Khan continue to deal with the perils of being undersized in an otherwise giant world.  They face bullying children, giant cats, sewer serpents, and the arbitrary destruction of their sole source of transportation.

Barda makes up her mind and decides to detonate the chemical factory.  Kathy Ferber catches her leaving the house with a mysterious package and comes to the scandalous conclusion that Barda is having an affair.  The warrioress is arrested post-destruction.  While in jail, Ted Kord delivers some unfortunate news.  Under the belief that the impersonating robot  destroyed in JLA #39 was the real Mister Miracle, he informs Barda Free that her husband is dead.
name: The Sewer Sticks
How Can I Say You're Missing If You Won't Go Away
The Lump That Came to Campus

One of the very first comic books ever made Tip Top was put out by the United Features which owned the rights to a large number of newspaper comic strips.

The features of Tip Top came from there.

In the end publication would be given over to Dell Publication and as such would see the new characters of Charlie Brown & Snoopy in it's pages shortly after that strip started in news papers in 1951.

I would also for most of it's run feature Tarzan.
One of the first comics from the so-called "Platinum Age" of comics.

description: Top Cow launches its biggest summer event to date with the return of Cyberforce and Hunter-Killer! When two fan-favorite antagonists join forces, both teams are thrust back into the spotlight and must band together to keep the world safe. But can they get along long enough to succeed? This FCBD09 preview issue leads directly into the five-issue event series launching in July and features an original story by Waid and Rocafort, plus special sneak-peeks of this year's "Pilot Season" contenders.
name: First Look

description: Was he even worth saving? Did she even save the right person? Shadow may find she acted to hastily in her attempt at heroism. Unfortunately she has caught the attention of someone that knows just how to deal with such a menace to society and it can only end in death. Not even Shadow has the power to challenge this new threat. The tables have turned and for the first time, rather than be saved, Shadow is in need of saving.
name: Book 3

description:
All-new story and art from fan-favorite writer/artist Erik Larsen (Spider-Man, Wolverine)! There's a new vigilante in town: The Dynamic Daredevil! This recently resurrected hero from comics' Golden Age has made Chicago his new home and it pits him against Chicago's fin-headed finest! Plus a mysterious assassin from Dragon's past is introduced as Dragon's battle against the notorious Vicious Circle heats up! It's the ultimate introductory issue and fit for readers young and old!

The Savage Dragon must team up with the Dynamic Daredevil to rescue his children from an unknown evil.
name: Daredevil

description: Story continued from Star Brand #12. Two years ago a phenomenon dubbed the White Event changed the New Universe forever. Humans began to develop super-human abilities all over the world. They became known as Paranormal. Last night, Kenneth Connell, possessor of the Starbrand and most powerful of all the Paranormals, tried to place the Brand on an inanimate object. The result...another White Event. Except this time the entire city of Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania was destroyed in the process. Thousands of souls snuffed out in an instant. All that remains is a gigantic crater and an unnatural maelstrom. This is the story of what happens next. Is this the beginning of the end for the New Universe? Yes.
name: GN

description: The source of Jeremy's problems reavealed; a demon activated by a curse placed on an ancestor over 300 years ago.
